{"metadata":{"externalID":"s:3GIO16ResourceProtocolP","modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"title":"ResourceProtocol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ResourceProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"symbolKind":"protocol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"ResourceProtocol"}],"role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Protocol"},"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Instance-Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ResourceProtocol\/resource_ptr-718oi"],"generated":true,"title":"Instance Properties"},{"generated":true,"title":"Instance Methods","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ResourceProtocol\/Register()","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ResourceProtocol\/Unregister()","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ResourceProtocol\/enumerateChildren(path:lookupFlags:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ResourceProtocol\/getInfo(path:lookupFlags:size:flags:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ResourceProtocol\/hasChildren(path:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ResourceProtocol\/lookupData(path:lookupFlags:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ResourceProtocol\/openStream(path:lookupFlags:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ResourceProtocol\/ref()","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ResourceProtocol\/resourcesRegister()","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ResourceProtocol\/resourcesUnregister()","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ResourceProtocol\/unref()"],"anchor":"Instance-Methods"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO"]]},"relationshipsSections":[{"title":"Inherits From","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/4GLib14PointerWrapperP"],"type":"inheritsFrom","kind":"relationships"},{"title":"Conforming Types","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Resource","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ResourceRef"],"type":"conformingTypes","kind":"relationships"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"ResourceProtocol"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"PointerWrapper","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib14PointerWrapperP"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GResource"},{"type":"text","text":" API and the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"glib-compile-resources.html","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" program provide a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"convenient and efficient alternative to this which has some nice properties."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"You maintain the files as normal files, so it’s easy to edit them, but during"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the build the files are combined into a binary bundle that is linked into the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"executable. This means that loading the resource files are efficient (as they","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"are already in memory, shared with other instances) and simple (no need to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"check for things like I\/O errors or locate the files in the filesystem). It","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"also makes it easier to create relocatable applications."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Resource files can also be marked as compressed. Such files will be included"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"in the resource bundle in a compressed form, but will be automatically"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"uncompressed when the resource is used. This is very useful e.g. for larger"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"text files that are parsed once (or rarely) and then thrown away.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Resource files can also be marked to be preprocessed, by setting the value of the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"preprocess","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" attribute to a comma-separated list of preprocessing options."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"The only options currently supported are:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"xml-stripblanks","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" which will use the "},{"identifier":"man:xmllint(1)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" command","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to strip ignorable whitespace from the XML file. For this to work,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the ","type":"text"},{"code":"XMLLINT","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" environment variable must be set to the full path to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the xmllint executable, or xmllint must be in the ","type":"text"},{"code":"PATH","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"; otherwise","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the preprocessing step is skipped."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"to-pixdata"},{"text":" (deprecated since gdk-pixbuf 2.32) which will use the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"gdk-pixbuf-pixdata","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" command to convert images to the "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/docs.gtk.org\/gdk-pixbuf\/class.Pixdata.html","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"format, which allows you to create pixbufs directly using the data inside","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the resource file, rather than an (uncompressed) copy of it. For this, the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"gdk-pixbuf-pixdata"},{"type":"text","text":" program must be in the "},{"code":"PATH","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", or the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GDK_PIXBUF_PIXDATA"},{"type":"text","text":" environment variable must be set to the full path to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the ","type":"text"},{"code":"gdk-pixbuf-pixdata","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" executable; otherwise the resource compiler will","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"abort. ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"to-pixdata"},{"text":" has been deprecated since gdk-pixbuf 2.32, as","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GResource"},{"type":"text","text":" supports embedding modern image formats just as well. Instead"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"of using it, embed a PNG or SVG file in your "},{"code":"GResource","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"json-stripblanks"},{"type":"text","text":" which will use the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"man:json-glib-format(1)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" command to strip ignorable"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"whitespace from the JSON file. For this to work, the "},{"code":"JSON_GLIB_FORMAT","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"environment variable must be set to the full path to the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"json-glib-format"},{"text":" executable, or it must be in the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PATH"},{"text":"; otherwise the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"preprocessing step is skipped. In addition, at least version 1.6 of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"json-glib-format"},{"type":"text","text":" is required."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Resource files will be exported in the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GResource"},{"text":" namespace using the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"combination of the given "},{"code":"prefix","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and the filename from the ","type":"text"},{"code":"file","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" element."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"alias"},{"type":"text","text":" attribute can be used to alter the filename to expose them at a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"different location in the resource namespace. Typically, this is used to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"include files from a different source directory without exposing the source"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"directory in the resource namespace, as in the example below."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Resource bundles are created by the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"glib-compile-resources.html","type":"reference","overridingTitle":"glib-compile-resources","isActive":true,"overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"code":"glib-compile-resources","type":"codeVoice"}]},{"type":"text","text":" program"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"which takes an XML file that describes the bundle, and a set of files that"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the XML references. These are combined into a binary resource bundle."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"An example resource description:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"xml","code":["<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>","<gresources>","  <gresource prefix=\"\/org\/gtk\/Example\">","    <file>data\/splashscreen.png<\/file>","    <file compressed=\"true\">dialog.ui<\/file>","    <file preprocess=\"xml-stripblanks\">menumarkup.xml<\/file>","    <file alias=\"example.css\">data\/example.css<\/file>","  <\/gresource>","<\/gresources>"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This will create a resource bundle with the following files:"}]},{"syntax":null,"type":"codeListing","code":["\/org\/gtk\/Example\/data\/splashscreen.png","\/org\/gtk\/Example\/dialog.ui","\/org\/gtk\/Example\/menumarkup.xml","\/org\/gtk\/Example\/example.css"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that all resources in the process share the same namespace, so use"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Java-style path prefixes (like in the above example) to avoid conflicts."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can then use ","type":"text"},{"overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"code":"glib-compile-resources","type":"codeVoice"}],"identifier":"glib-compile-resources.html","isActive":true,"type":"reference","overridingTitle":"glib-compile-resources"},{"text":" to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"compile the XML to a binary bundle that you can load with","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.Resource.load"},{"text":"]. However, it’s more common to use the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"--generate-source"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"--generate-header","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" arguments to create a source file"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and header to link directly into your application.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This will generate "},{"code":"get_resource()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"register_resource()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unregister_resource()"},{"type":"text","text":" functions, prefixed by the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"--c-name"},{"text":" argument passed","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to "},{"identifier":"glib-compile-resources.html","type":"reference","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"code":"glib-compile-resources","type":"codeVoice"}],"overridingTitle":"glib-compile-resources","isActive":true},{"text":". ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"get_resource()"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"returns the generated "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GResource"},{"text":" object. The register and unregister","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"functions register the resource so its files can be accessed using"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[func","type":"text"},{"code":"Gio.resources_lookup_data","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"]."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Once a "},{"code":"GResource","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" has been created and registered all the data in it can be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"accessed globally in the process by using API calls like"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[func","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.resources_open_stream"},{"type":"text","text":"] to stream the data or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[func","type":"text"},{"code":"Gio.resources_lookup_data","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] to get a direct pointer to the data. You can"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"also use URIs like ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"resource:\/\/\/org\/gtk\/Example\/data\/splashscreen.png"},{"type":"text","text":" with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[iface"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/File"},{"type":"text","text":"] to access the resource data."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Some higher-level APIs, such as "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/docs.gtk.org\/gtk4\/class.Application.html","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"will automatically load resources from certain well-known paths in the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"resource namespace as a convenience. See the documentation for those APIs","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"for details.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"There are two forms of the generated source, the default version uses the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"compiler support for constructor and destructor functions (where available)"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"to automatically create and register the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GResource"},{"type":"text","text":" on startup or library"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"load time. If you pass ","type":"text"},{"code":"--manual-register","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", two functions to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"register\/unregister the resource are created instead. This requires an"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"explicit initialization call in your application\/library, but it works on all","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"platforms, even on the minor ones where constructors are not supported.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(Constructor support is available for at least Win32, Mac OS and Linux.)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that resource data can point directly into the data segment of e.g. a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"library, so if you are unloading libraries during runtime you need to be very"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"careful with keeping around pointers to data from a resource, as this goes","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"away when the library is unloaded. However, in practice this is not generally","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"a problem, since most resource accesses are for your own resources, and"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"resource data is often used once, during parsing, and then released."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","level":1,"text":"Overlays","anchor":"Overlays"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When debugging a program or testing a change to an installed version, it is"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"often useful to be able to replace resources in the program or library,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"without recompiling, for debugging or quick hacking and testing purposes."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Since GLib 2.50, it is possible to use the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_RESOURCE_OVERLAYS"},{"type":"text","text":" environment"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"variable to selectively overlay resources with replacements from the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"filesystem.  It is a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_SEARCHPATH_SEPARATOR"},{"type":"text","text":"-separated list of substitutions"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"to perform during resource lookups. It is ignored when running in a setuid","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"process.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A substitution has the form","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["\/org\/gtk\/libgtk=\/home\/desrt\/gtk-overlay"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":null},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The part before the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"="},{"text":" is the resource subpath for which the overlay","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"applies.  The part after is a filesystem path which contains files and"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"subdirectories as you would like to be loaded as resources with the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"equivalent names."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the example above, if an application tried to load a resource with the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"resource path "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\/org\/gtk\/libgtk\/ui\/gtkdialog.ui"},{"type":"text","text":" then "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GResource"},{"text":" would check","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the filesystem path ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\/home\/desrt\/gtk-overlay\/ui\/gtkdialog.ui"},{"type":"text","text":".  If a file was"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"found there, it would be used instead.  This is an overlay, not an outright"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"replacement, which means that if a file is not found at that path, the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"built-in version will be used instead.  Whiteouts are not currently","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"supported.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Substitutions must start with a slash, and must not contain a trailing slash"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"before the ","type":"text"},{"code":"=","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":".  The path after the slash should ideally be absolute, but"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"this is not strictly required.  It is possible to overlay the location of a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"single resource with an individual file.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ResourceProtocol","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" protocol exposes the methods and properties of an underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GResource"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"The default implementation of these can be found in the protocol extension below."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"For a concrete class that implements these methods and properties, see "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Resource","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Alternatively, use ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ResourceRef"},{"text":" as a lighweight, ","type":"text"},{"code":"unowned","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" reference if you already have an instance you just want to use."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"abstract":[{"text":"Applications and libraries often contain binary or textual data that is","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"really part of the application, rather than user data. For instance"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/docs.gtk.org\/gtk4\/class.Builder.html"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".ui"},{"text":" files,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"splashscreen images, [class"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Menu","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"] markup XML, CSS files, icons, etc."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"These are often shipped as files in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"$datadir\/appname"},{"text":", or manually","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"included as literal strings in the code.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ResourceProtocol"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/resourceprotocol"]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/File":{"abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GFile"},{"type":"text","text":" is a high level abstraction for manipulating files on a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"virtual file system. "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GFile"},{"type":"text","text":"s are lightweight, immutable objects"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that do no I\/O upon creation. It is necessary to understand that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GFile"},{"type":"text","text":" objects do not represent files, merely an identifier for a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"file. All file content I\/O is implemented as streaming operations"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(see [class","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/InputStream","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":"] and [class","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/OutputStream"},{"type":"text","text":"])."}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/file","title":"File","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"File","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"File"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/File"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/ResourceProtocol":{"kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"ResourceProtocol"}],"role":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Applications and libraries often contain binary or textual data that is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"really part of the application, rather than user data. For instance","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/docs.gtk.org\/gtk4\/class.Builder.html","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".ui"},{"type":"text","text":" files,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"splashscreen images, [class","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Menu"},{"type":"text","text":"] markup XML, CSS files, icons, etc."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"These are often shipped as files in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"$datadir\/appname"},{"text":", or manually","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"included as literal strings in the code.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ResourceProtocol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/resourceprotocol","title":"ResourceProtocol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ResourceProtocol","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/ResourceProtocol/resource_ptr-718oi":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Typed pointer to the underlying "},{"code":"GResource","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol","title":"resource_ptr","defaultImplementations":1,"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"resource_ptr","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"UnsafeMutablePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sp"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"text":"GResource","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":">!"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/resourceprotocol\/resource_ptr-718oi","kind":"symbol","required":true,"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ResourceProtocol\/resource_ptr-718oi"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/ResourceProtocol/getInfo(path:lookupFlags:size:flags:)":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Looks for a file at the specified "},{"code":"path","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" in the resource and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"if found returns information about it."}],"title":"getInfo(path:lookupFlags:size:flags:)","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ResourceProtocol\/getInfo(path:lookupFlags:size:flags:)","url":"\/documentation\